<p class="govuk-body">The account header is used for services that are part of the <a class="govuk-link" href="https://www.tax.service.gov.uk/personal-account">personal tax account</a>.</p>

<h2 id="when-to-use" class="govuk-heading-l">When to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Use this pattern if your service is part of the personal tax account.</p>

<h2 id="when-not-to-use" class="govuk-heading-l">When not to use</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">Do not use this pattern if your service is not part of the personal tax account. Use the <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/header/">GOV.UK header</a> instead.</p>

<h2 id="how-it-works" class="govuk-heading-l">How it works</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">The account header contains:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>the GOV.UK cookie banner, with a <a href="https://www.tax.service.gov.uk/help/cookies">link to HMRC cookie policy</a></li>
  <li>the <a class="govuk-link" href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/header/">GOV.UK header</a></li>
  <li>the account menu</li>
  <li>the Welsh language toggle, if your service is available in Welsh</li>
</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">There are 2 ways to use the account header. You can use HTML or, if you are using Nunjucks or <a class="govuk-link" href="https://govuk-prototype-kit.herokuapp.com">version 7 or later of the GOV.UK Prototype Kit</a>, you can use the Nunjucks macro.</p>

